subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum: Subrectangular, transverse, almost twice as wide as it is long (L/W ratio: 
0.61
) and slightly wider than the head. Disc very slightly convex, divided lenghtways by a distinct but shallow medial sulcus. Transverse microsculpture. Anterior margin slightly convex, being its anterior angles round shaped. Basal margin slightly convex. Lateral margins curved, with its maximum width at the level of the anterior marginal setae, slightly sinuous in basal third. Posterior angles obtuse, blunt and dorsally projected. Lateral channel wide, shallow and gradually spread to the posterior angles. Bassal fossae deep but with poor defined outline. Two setae on each side, at basal angle and before the middle.
